obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (68326)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Agriculturists to be sued where they reside.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00099_187917_1663829896037&sectionId=68326&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00099_187917_1663829896037
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Every suit of the description mentioned in`
  line `Section 3, clause (w)^1, may, if the defendant, or, when there are several defendants, one only of`
  line `such defendants, is an agriculturist, be instituted and tried in a Court within the local limits of`
  line `whose jurisdiction such defendant resides, and not elsewhere.`
  line
  line `Every such suit in which there are several defendants who are agriculturists may be instituted and tried`
  line `in a Court within the local limits of whose jurisdiction any one of such defendants resides, and not`
  line elsewhere.
  line `Nothing herein contained shall affect sections 22 to 25 (both inclusive) of the ^1Code of Civil Procedure.`
  line
  line `[* * *]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Reproduced below:`
  line
  line `"(w) suits for the recovery of money alleged to be due to the plaintiff--`
  line
  line `on account of money lent or advanced to, or paid for, the defendant, or as the price of goods sold, or`
  line
  line `on an account stated between the plaintiff and defendant, or`
  line
  line `on a written or unwritten engagement for the payment of money not hereinbefore provided for;".`
  line
  line `2. See now Act 5 of 1908.`
